      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Logistics Management Inbound
Process: LI-200-040 Rework Material
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-618993A9-E618-49A8-BA97-D3DD6F402B7E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Rework or Repair Materials Process Steps –
1.Identify materials flagged for rework or repair during the quality inspection processes
2.Document the defects and reasons that require the rework or repair
3.Create a Rework or Repair Order, this would be Subcontracting PO configured for rework or repair
4.Plan and Schedule the rework or repair tasks considering the availability of materials, and resources
5.Issue the materials from inventory to the rework or repair order
6.Perform the rework or repair tasks as specified
7.Once the repair or rework is done and the material passes the quality inspection, complete the order in the system
8.Post the reworked/ repaired materials back into inventory using a goods receipt
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-6E30F9A7-B767-4B3E-B4C7-05456D9496F1" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Execute Rework or Repair activities mentioned in the Order
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-6CA9DEE1-3F09-4AA1-9DFE-F5D5D0F0DF0D" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Johnson, Graeme &lt;graeme.johnson@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
